Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.52,0:00:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\pos(316,325)\fad(400,0)}Obey the Rules and manners\Nto have a fun Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.19,0:00:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the Duel Monsters World,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.15,0:00:09.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}we got a Legendary Dragon card.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.94,0:00:14.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But we still have no clues\Nabout the enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.20,0:00:18.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then, Pegasus gave us\Nan invitation to America.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.83,0:00:23.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When we meet Pegasus,\N we might know who the enemy is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.00,0:00:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meanwhile, Kaiba-{\i0}kun{\i1} has set out to meet Pegasus as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.33,0:00:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Sometime ago, for the sake of living, we left behind our happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.29,0:00:56.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We deceived ourselves, clinging to this mere illusion as we danced...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.59,0:01:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With closed eyes, at the end of the horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.85,0:01:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was searching for your smiling face...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.31,0:01:16.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We embrace our dreams and continue on...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.32,0:01:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}within the swaying traces of memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.25,0:01:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someday, I will once again grasp hold of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.34,0:01:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}these feelings I have locked away in my heart... Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.09,0:02:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Nightmare of Toon World"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.38,0:02:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.15,0:02:13.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're getting close to\Ndowntown San Fransisco.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.41,0:02:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so excited!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.90,0:02:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first time\N I've been to America!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.49,0:02:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gosh, you aren't here for sightseeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.75,0:02:22.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You seem a bit distracted, Partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.15,0:02:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.02,0:02:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm worried about Pegasus's expression on the video letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.75,0:02:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He looked like he was\Nbeing followed by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.65,0:02:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm certainly concerned about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.65,0:02:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.85,0:02:51.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duelist Kingdom...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.05,0:02:53.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think I'd ever\N come {\i1}here{\i0} again...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.19,0:02:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.65,0:03:01.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking at this place, all that comes to mind is a lot of horrible memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.11,0:03:35.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems like no one's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.92,0:03:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph. It's better if there's\N no one to interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.61,0:03:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Mokuba.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.74,0:03:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.58,0:04:15.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a cable car!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.91,0:04:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like the ones\N you see in the movies!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.78,0:04:25.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa! I can see the Golden Gate Bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.99,0:04:30.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It gives you the feeling you're in America!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.04,0:04:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Yugi?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.66,0:04:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.62,0:04:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with you?\NAre you thinking about something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.72,0:04:35.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.72,0:04:39.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm thinking about\Nwhat Pegasus wants to tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.84,0:04:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monsters appearing\N all over the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.28,0:04:45.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the God Cards were stolen...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.48,0:04:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And these guys calling themselves the Musketeers of Doma appeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.15,0:04:55.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the crisis between the Duel Monsters World and our world.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.52,0:04:58.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pegasus must know something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.82,0:05:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What could it be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.25,0:05:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calling us out here and not having the courtesy to show yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.22,0:05:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about {\i1}rude{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.01,0:05:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit the bullshit and\N get out here this instant!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.27,0:05:36.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome, Kaiba boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.28,0:05:38.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Long time no see!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.72,0:05:50.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you, Kaiba boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.62,0:05:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.01,0:05:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokuba boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.98,0:05:56.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you finally appeared, Pegasus.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.46,0:05:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have something\N I must confirm with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.55,0:06:00.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.91,0:06:05.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the strange events occurring around the world were caused by Industrial Illusions, were they not?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.72,0:06:06.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.84,0:06:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't play dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.30,0:06:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am talking about the incident with Duel Monsters appearing on their own!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.35,0:06:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no problem with my Kaiba Corporation's Solid Vision System!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.23,0:06:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So who else could it be other than the creator of Duel Monsters himself?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.02,0:06:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It couldn't be anyone {\i1}but{\i0} you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.95,0:06:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}do{\i0} wonder about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.90,0:06:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.15,0:06:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.82,0:06:34.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All responsibility falls on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.18,0:06:35.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.25,0:06:37.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.96,0:06:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.38,0:06:44.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to know the answer,\Ndefeat me in a Duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.75,0:06:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.05,0:06:49.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember the Duel I shared with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.68,0:06:54.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You devoted yourself to saving Mokuba boy's soul that eventful day~
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.35,0:07:01.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mokuba boy's soul\N has been sealed in this card.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.40,0:07:07.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba boy, if you can defeat me
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.23,0:07:11.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will release Mokuba boy's soul from the sealed card.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.45,0:07:16.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you couldn't defeat me then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.95,0:07:18.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And {\i1}then{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.66,0:07:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kaiba boy, I presume you are aware of what it means to lose a game?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.88,0:07:27.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The loser loses {\b0}everything{\b1}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.13,0:07:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What is precious to them...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.05,0:07:30.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And even {\b0}themselves{\b1}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.13,0:07:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You shall suffer the\N same fate as Mokuba boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.68,0:07:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mind Card!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.10,0:07:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut your mouth!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.86,0:07:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so angry, Kaiba boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.61,0:07:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just telling you the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.94,0:07:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plotting to throw me off by bringing up past humiliations is nothing but a waste of breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.66,0:07:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring it, Pegasus! It's about time we settled the score once and for all!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.83,0:08:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine by me, Kaiba boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.71,0:08:05.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We shall enjoy the greatest Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.08,0:08:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since you have come all this way to Duelist Kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.40,0:08:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have prepared for you\Na nostalgic Duel Ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.90,0:08:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am sure you would\N love to have your revenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.65,0:08:33.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could care less \Nwhat system I Duel with,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.49,0:08:35.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I just can't {\i1}trust{\i0} you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.03,0:08:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll be using {\i1}this{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.70,0:08:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no possible {\i1}way{\i0} you can beat me in a fight using fair conditions!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.08,0:08:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.87,0:08:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My brother won't lose\N to someone like {\i1}you{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.46,0:08:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds {\i1}fabulous{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.05,0:08:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We will know very shortly whether those words hold any weight to them or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.01,0:08:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mokuba, you stay back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.38,0:08:56.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.78,0:09:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Pegasus we're talking about. No one knows what he's up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.06,0:09:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.69,0:09:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have {\i1}no{\i0} idea of how long I've been {\i1}dreaming{\i0} of this day...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.70,0:09:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He sealed away his mindset as a Duelist before...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.03,0:09:23.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But my brother's going to unleash it once again!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.29,0:09:24.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.83,0:09:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kick Pegasus' ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.42,0:09:32.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you fiend! Have you set up another cheap trick to look at my hand again?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.59,0:09:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.84,0:09:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please do not worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.59,0:09:40.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Defeating {\i1}you{\i0} without the aid of my Mind Scan is like taking a walk in the park!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.35,0:09:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't kid yourself now!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.97,0:09:44.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what you're up to, but {\i1}I'll{\i0} be the one to win!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.14,0:09:48.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.77,0:09:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel!!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.74,0:09:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I take the first move.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.88,0:10:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.16,0:10:05.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon a Monster in Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.29,0:10:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That card...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.29,0:10:11.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I set a reverse card and...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.17,0:10:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...complete my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.00,0:10:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Humph! What a {\i1}show off{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.96,0:10:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.38,0:10:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you say this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.43,0:10:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You played the same opening move you did in our first Duel,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.01,0:10:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to try and\N sway my battle strategies?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.10,0:10:25.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...! Is that {\i1}so{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.52,0:10:28.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry! I forgot {\i1}all about it{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.69,0:10:30.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you before!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.56,0:10:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm an entirelly different person than I was back then!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.27,0:10:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your psychological warfare won't work on me any more!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.53,0:10:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.49,0:10:41.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Spear Dragon in Attack Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.87,0:10:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Toon Alligator!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.75,0:10:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the Special Ability of Spear Dragon,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.46,0:10:57.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When it attacks a Monster with Defense Points lower than its Attack Points,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.76,0:11:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Player will receive the difference as damage to their Life Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.78,0:11:06.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, after it attacks, it switches to Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.64,0:11:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set two reverse cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.85,0:11:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.65,0:11:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good job, Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.33,0:11:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rare cards~
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.83,0:11:34.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,IT {\i1}STINKS{\i0}~!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.42,0:11:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It hurts~
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.09,0:11:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who're {\i1}you{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.85,0:11:48.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.72,0:11:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.64,0:11:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,HELP ME~!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.93,0:12:06.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.13,0:12:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! This card should put a little spunk in our funk!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.03,0:12:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card, Toon Table of Contents!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.13,0:12:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toon Table of Contents?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.10,0:12:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can take a card with "Toon" in its name and add it from my deck to my hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.43,0:12:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.97,0:12:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.64,0:12:30.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.23,0:12:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As expected of Kaiba boy!\N You are very clever!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.19,0:12:37.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This invincible card's name is...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.53,0:12:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toon World!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.63,0:12:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.16,0:12:46.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll once again invite you to the world of perfect beings!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.74,0:12:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I pay 1000 points as a cost,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.78,0:12:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in order to activate Toon World!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.21,0:13:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I then Summon Toon Masked Sorcerer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.05,0:13:08.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can only use Toon Monsters to attack or defend against other Toon Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.06,0:13:11.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the Toon World that caused my brother great suffering...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.46,0:13:14.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is he gonna fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.23,0:13:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attacks from Normal Monsters \Ncan't harm Toon Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.36,0:13:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You {\i1}really{\i0} think the\N same trick will work twice?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.50,0:13:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse Trap activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.26,0:13:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Clone Token!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.63,0:13:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaiba boy has also\N Summoned a Toon Monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.91,0:13:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack as you wish!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.10,0:13:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll just destroy both Toon Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.83,0:13:38.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goddamn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.06,0:13:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hold the data of every Duel I've ever played in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.17,0:13:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And of course, I have analyzed a new strategy to use against you from that information.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.26,0:13:49.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's perfect!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.60,0:13:51.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I end my turn...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.56,0:13:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.33,0:13:56.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't intend to fight you\N on your own turf!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.19,0:14:00.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sacrifice Toon Masked Sorcerer and Spear Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.94,0:14:01.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.77,0:14:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think you are doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.11,0:14:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Blue-Eyes White Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.12,0:14:15.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother's Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.96,0:14:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll obtain victory alongside my Blue-Eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.88,0:14:21.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.43,0:14:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's Blue-Eyes attacking, it won't work against a Toon's Effect!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.05,0:14:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not scared of your Toons!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.26,0:14:30.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I told you my Duel strategy is perfect?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.72,0:14:33.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I activate a Reverse Trap!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.10,0:14:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toon Mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.39,0:14:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card lets me sacrifice my own Toon Monster,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.61,0:14:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Special Summon a Toon Monster exact copy of the opponent's Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.07,0:14:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.26,0:14:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's name is Blue-Eyes Toon Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.58,0:14:58.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Blue-Eyes Toon Dragon...!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.08,0:15:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You actually placed this disgusting form in front of me again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.42,0:15:04.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! What cruel words to utter!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.34,0:15:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make my repeat myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.63,0:15:08.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a strategy\N to deal with your Toons!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.72,0:15:11.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Magic Card, activate!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.26,0:15:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shrink!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.29,0:15:19.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now the Attack Power of Blue-Eyes Toon Dragon will be slashed by 1500 points!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.56,0:15:22.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But my Toons are the ultimate life forms!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.27,0:15:25.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you slash their Attack Points with Shrink, it's meaningless!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.66,0:15:30.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll then activate the Continuous Magic Card from my hand, Card Treasure of Lamentation!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.66,0:15:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I use Blue-Eyes White Dragon to attack Toon Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.95,0:15:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasted effort!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.75,0:15:44.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you looking to repeat the same stupid mistake you made in the past?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.42,0:15:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Burst Stream of Destruction!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.63,0:15:54.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you forgotten already?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.05,0:15:57.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normal attacks\N don't work on Toon Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.30,0:16:00.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph! I know that better than anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.23,0:16:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm aiming for something {\i1}else{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.14,0:16:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.56,0:16:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Continuous Magic, Card Treasure of Lamentation!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.90,0:16:11.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During your Battle Phase, when one of your Monsters attacks and destroys the opponent's Monster,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.65,0:16:15.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can add one card\N from my deck to my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.03,0:16:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I have a key card in my Deck capable of destroying Toon World...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.79,0:16:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm doing this so I can draw it faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.17,0:16:25.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.08,0:16:28.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pay 500 Life as the cost...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.26,0:16:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Blue-Eyes Toon Dragon can Direct Attack you, Kaiba boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.97,0:16:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have\Nany Toons on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.10,0:16:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You cannot avoid this attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.68,0:16:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse Magic, Attack Nullification!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.15,0:16:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.02,0:16:50.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can use this card when the opposing Monster attacks,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.11,0:16:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then negate that attack and end the Battle Phase!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.82,0:16:56.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't make a {\i1}bit{\i0} of difference whether it's a Toon attacking or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.00,0:16:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll use a Magic Card...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.45,0:17:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toon Rollback, activate now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.62,0:17:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have two chances\Nin the Battle Phase now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.00,0:17:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.86,0:17:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monsters can attack only once per turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.19,0:17:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you get a second Battle Phase,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.09,0:17:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can't attack me with him again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.01,0:17:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.85,0:17:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.10,0:17:25.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am yet to Summon\N a Monster on this turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.69,0:17:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.10,0:17:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it will be no problem for me to Summon a Monster on this turn! {\i1}Mondaiarimasen{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.73,0:17:35.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, I sacrifice Blue-Eyes Toon Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.16,0:17:39.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Toon Black Magician Girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.25,0:17:53.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Direct Attack the player!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.05,0:17:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.35,0:18:01.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.37,0:18:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe he lost 2000 Life in just one shot...!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.81,0:18:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.14,0:18:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Toons have evolved!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.86,0:18:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.48,0:18:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.07,0:18:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use my Blue-Eyes to attack Toon Black Magician Girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.70,0:18:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He can't defeat the Toon by attacking with Blue-Eyes this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.45,0:18:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.79,0:18:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,NO, NO, NO, NO, NO!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.00,0:18:37.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tada~!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.63,0:18:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of Card Treasure of Lamentation, I draw one card...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.60,0:18:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever is so funny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.60,0:18:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Perfect beings"? That's worth a {\i1}big laugh{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.60,0:18:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to tarnish your title as the creator of Duel Monsters like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.73,0:18:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.53,0:19:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can admit as much that Toon Monsters are invincible, but only under the protection of Toon World!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.76,0:19:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I just have to destroy Toon World!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.49,0:19:06.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toon World?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.16,0:19:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the Magic Card!\N A Wingbeat of Giant Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.92,0:19:13.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.96,0:19:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This card lets you return a Level 5 or higher Dragon-Type Monster to your hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.76,0:19:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and in exchange destroy every Magic and Trap Card on the field!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.39,0:19:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So your beloved Toon World will now disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.73,0:19:41.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Toon World has...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.54,0:19:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.82,0:19:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no card\Ncapable of defeating me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.66,0:19:47.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're amazing, Big brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.45,0:19:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll also Summon God Of Destruction - Vasago\N in Defense Mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.42,0:19:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn end!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.13,0:20:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.62,0:20:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true my Toon destruction\N plan was flawless,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.43,0:20:09.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you should have fully understood the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.81,0:20:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All you're doing is simply imitating his previous style of Dueling.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.52,0:20:18.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Pegasus I know isn't {\i1}that{\i0} dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.44,0:20:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're {\i1}not{\i0} Pegasus!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.45,0:20:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell {\i1}are{\i0} you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.28,0:20:24.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.41,0:20:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I expected no less of Seto Kaiba.\N You saw right through my disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.12,0:20:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.29,0:20:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm {\i1}not{\i0} Pegasus.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.09,0:20:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.63,0:20:43.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am one of the\N Musketeers of Doma! Amelda!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.76,0:20:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doma? Musketeers?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.39,0:20:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't forgive you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.64,0:20:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.22,0:20:54.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my revenge... Seto Kaiba!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.32,0:21:01.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Activate now! Barrier of Orichalcos!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.53,0:21:07.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.23,0:21:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.23,0:21:20.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What on Earth is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.87,0:21:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Barrier of Orichalcos!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.67,0:21:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ones imprisoned within this barrier
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.51,0:21:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can't escape until someone wins the Duel!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.64,0:21:33.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the one to lose...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.38,0:21:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His soul will be sealed \Nwithin the boundary!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.06,0:21:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.60,0:21:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seto Kaiba...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.09,0:21:44.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By order of the king of Doma, Lord Dartz...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.28,0:21:46.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I shall claim your soul!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.14,0:22:02.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The houses lined down the street drifting by being dyed red
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.50,0:22:10.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I notice pain, it'll turn into happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.11,0:22:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Every time people wipe away tears, they understand bonds
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.18,0:22:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The warm strength that you gave me will change into kindness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.66,0:22:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Overflowing feelings don't stop
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.94,0:22:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll live while I feel it, for me to be myself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.84,0:22:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Healed by overflowing friendship
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.99,0:23:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our fated encounter is a truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.51,0:23:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and someday we'll be able to understand each other
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.23,0:23:23.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have come to America in order to meet with Pegasus.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.13,0:23:26.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But our ride suddenly comes to a stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.01,0:23:27.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the driver takes off somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.80,0:23:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Industrial Illusions really out here in the middle of nowhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.55,0:23:35.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Elsewhere, the impostor Pegasus finally reveals his true identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.72,0:23:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This "Amelda" seems to hold a strong grudge against Kaiba-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.81,0:23:41.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen between them in the past?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.40,0:23:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.98,0:23:44.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Wake Up! Critias"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.69,0:23:45.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Duel standby!
